      "amount": "1 tablespoon",
      "notes": null
    }
  ],
  "instructions": [
    "Preheat the oven to 375°F (190°C).",
    "Mix together the palm sugar, ghee, and roasted chicken breast in a large bowl.",
    "Add the parsley, green chili peppers, coconut oil, salt, and black pepper to the bowl and mix well.",
    "Pour the mixture into a 9x13 inch baking dish and smooth the top.",
    "Drizzle the lacquer glaze over the top of the dish.",
    "Bake in the preheated oven for 30-40 minutes or until the top is golden brown and the dish is hot and bubbly.",
    "Remove from the oven and let cool for a few minutes before serving."
